- 'analyst' refers to a user role in the system;
- 'least frequent visitor' refers to the minimum total access count for the analyst role;
- 'most popular stock flowers' refers to the top-accessed stock symbols.

- "guardians of the digital realm" refers to users with the role of 'admin' or similar high-access roles;
- "elevated permissions" refers to users with an access level greater than 2;
- "traversed the portal" refers to access log entries in the system;
- "more than once" means the user has more than one access log entry.

- "explorer" refers to the user who has the highest number of access logs and the longest total duration of access sessions;
- "dive deep into the ocean of financial data" refers to accessing stock information frequently and for extended periods;
- "navigating a particular stock's waves" refers to accessing a specific stock more frequently than others.

- 'Recently viewed' refers to the top 3 most recent access records for each user;
- 'Active traders' are users who have accessed the system and viewed technology stocks;
- 'More than one type of interaction' implies that users have performed actions other than just viewing on the same day.

- "peered into the secrets of the year" refers to users who have viewed data in the current year;
- "gatekeepers with keys more than two" refers to users with an access level greater than 2;
- "garden of departments" refers to the organization's departments.

- 'most active' refers to the user with the highest number of access log entries;
- 'highest level of access' refers to an access level of 3;
- 'trader' refers to a user with the role 'trader'.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT stock_symbol, sector
FROM stocks
WHERE market_cap > 100000000000.0;
